          <p>Hello everyone,</p>
<p>We’d like to call your attention to a recent <a href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!topic/envoy-announce/jlNq3_aXx4E" rel="nofollow noopener">Envoy announcement</a> that affects Istio:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Envoy security team would like to announce the forthcoming release of Envoy 1.11.1.</p>
<p>This release will be made available on Tuesday, the 13th of August 2019 at 10:00 PDT (17:00 GMT).<br>
This release will fix 5 security defect(s), all of them considered HIGH severity.</p>
<p>No further details or patches will be made available in advance of the release.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>At the same time the Envoy community makes 1.11.1 available (August 13th at 10am PDT), the Istio team will publish Istio 1.2.4 and 1.1.13 containing fixes for the same 5 defects.</p>
<ul>
<li>The Istio Product Security Committee</li>
</ul>
